  "_doc": "Lorwyn Eclipsed (ECL) Play + Collector recipes from Wizards' 'Collecting Lorwyn Eclipsed' article (https://magic.wizards.com/en/news/feature/collecting-lorwyn-eclipsed). ECL has Play + Collector Boosters and NO Draft Booster (authoritative). Set codes: ECL = main set, ECC = Lorwyn Eclipsed Commander, TECL = tokens, AECL = Art Series. Approximations: Special Guests (20 cards) referenced via the 'special_guest' filter on the main set rather than a dedicated promo code. 'Fable frame' showcase cards approximated with the 'showcase' filter. Japan Showcase cards approximated with 'showcase' + 'japanese'. The 1% fracture-foil Japan Showcase chase now targets the named 'fracture_foil' finish precisely (the article calls it a 'fracture foil Japan Showcase card'); this trades the 'japanese' lang predicate for the distinct finish. The serialized Bitterbloom Bearer's 'double rainbow foil' has no Scryfall finish predicate, so it stays on the 'serialized' filter. Borderless nonland + borderless reversible shock lands fold into the 'borderless' filter. AUDIT 2026-06: Special Guests outcomes re-pointed to set SPG + spg_ecl (collector range — sheets verified by release date). The previous special_guest promo filter matched zero prints, and unranged SPG pulls would leak other sets’ guests. AUDIT 2026-06: special-finish outcome rarities corrected to match the actual printed sheets (pool-verified): fracture_foil->mythic. AUDIT 2026-06 (article re-verification): commons SPG converted from per-slot to per-pack (1-in-55 boosters → 0.26%/slot, was ~12.7%/pack); land slot regained its full-art half (default 40/10 + full-art 40/10, was basics-only 40/10); fable-frame and borderless/shock minors added to wildcard, rare/mythic, and foil slots per the published tables; both Collector Booster Fun slots rebuilt verbatim (extended-art mythics removed — none printed; foil SPG corrected 4.5→10.5).",
